		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Dear Viewers,</p>

<p>Last week we changed our Video Player to make your viewing of my videos much better. I also included a button at the end of each video text for you to send any video directly to your friends.</p>

<p><b>This process did not go as smoothly as I had hoped.</b></p>

<p>During this transition to the new video player, some customers in America and around the world could not access my BLOG site, or if they could, they could not play my most recent video on St. John's Wort.</p>

<p><b>The good news is that now my BLOG is fully up-and-running,</b> and the new video player is accessible to everyone around the world. I am truly sorry if you experienced any problems, and if you still do, please <a class="email" title="Email Tech Support" href="mailto:websupport@herbdoc.com?subject=Dr. Schulze's BLOG Video Problem&body=Dear Dr. Schulze BLOG Team: %0D%0DI am unable to view the videos. I am using __________* as my web browser.%0D%0DThank you,%0D%0D
%0D%0D*Please specify your web browser name and version # if possible (ex: Safari 5.1.9,%0D%0D
Firefox 3.6.15, etc.) so we can more quickly assist you and resolve the issue.">Contact Us</a> immediately.</p>

<p>Finally, because of this problem, I am running my <a href="http://herbdocblog.com/article/Video/medicinal-herbsst-johns-wort/">St. John's Wort Video</a> for an additional week, so everyone worldwide has a chance to view it. Next week, I will continue my new videos I am filming here in Italy!</p>

<p>Again, I am sorry for any inconvenience or problems you had trying to access my BLOG or in viewing the Videos.</p>

<p>— Dr. Schulze</p>]]></content:encoded>
